[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"461444\">Sam Mohr</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/231634-beginners/topic/Accumulating.20Ok.20values.20from.20List.20Result/near/449676541\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"701847\">Monica</span> try throwing the identity function at <a href=\"https://www.roc-lang.org/builtins/List#mapTry\">https://www.roc-lang.org/builtins/List#mapTry</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>whenever \"pass the identity function\" is the best answer, I always suspect there's a missing function in the API, and this seems like one of those situations <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 449696903,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1720375019
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what would be a good name for a function like this to add to <code>List</code>?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">err</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">ok</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">err</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 449696921,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1720375040
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>maybe <code>List.tryAll</code> or something like that?</p>",
        "id": 449696929,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1720375058
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>perhaps <code>List.try</code></p>",
        "id": 449696938,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1720375075
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Did these _already_ get \"tried\" by virtue of already being results (rather than tasks)? I don't recall if there's a naming precedent established for this kind of thing in Roc yet.</p>",
        "id": 449732190,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1720392996
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And does it make more sense to have lists know about results rather than results knowing about lists?</p>\n<p>A list seems more fundamental to me, thus the result module knowing about any number of things seems more natural than the list module knowing directly about list elements representing failure.</p>",
        "id": 449732348,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1720393190
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe adding the function to <strong>Result</strong>, like <strong>sequence</strong> with <strong>Task</strong> would be easier to learn.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">sequence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">err</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">ok</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">err</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 449938077,
        "sender_full_name": "Francois Green",
        "timestamp": 1720460421
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think for result specifically mirroring <code>Result.try</code> with <code>Result.tryAll</code> makes most sense.</p>",
        "id": 449938416,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1720460561
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>sequence/sequential</code> makes sense on <code>Task</code> cause they are actually run in order.</p>",
        "id": 449938524,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1720460596
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Results are already generated outputs. On top of that, this would only be for <code>List</code> not for generic sequences.</p>",
        "id": 449938577,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1720460626
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Result.tryAll</code> is a good option! I like that it is concise, but still tells the reader \"we're working with a list of results\". I think <code>List.try</code>is less obvious on that front.</p>",
        "id": 449952325,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1720463943
    }
]